ZH: 他偏要去那家餐厅吃晚饭。
EN: He insists on going to that restaurant for dinner.

ZH: 她偏爱喝咖啡而不是茶。
EN: She has a preference for coffee over tea.

ZH: 孩子们偏爱玩电子游戏。
EN: The children tend to prefer playing video games.

ZH: 我偏要去看这部电影。
EN: I have a strong desire to watch this movie.

ZH: 老板偏好使用电子邮件而不是电话。
EN: The boss prefers using email over phone calls.

ZH: 我们偏向支持这个计划。
EN: We tend to lean towards supporting this plan.

ZH: 他偏爱大海而不是山区。
EN: He favors the sea over the mountains.

ZH: 妈妈偏心地对待姐姐。
EN: Mom shows partiality towards my older sister.

ZH: 那位老师偏向于格罗夫红色。
EN: That teacher tends to favor the color burgundy.

ZH: 我们偏向认为这是一个好主意。
EN: We tend to think this is a good idea.

ZH: 警察偏好驾驶黑色的警车。
EN: The police officer prefers driving a black patrol car.

ZH: 我们偏向于选择这个品牌。
EN: We tend to choose this brand over others.

ZH: 他偏爱吃辣的食物。
EN: He has a preference for spicy food.

ZH: 那位球员偏好使用左手。
EN: That player prefers using his left hand.

ZH: 我们偏向支持绿色环保措施。
EN: We tend to support green environmental measures.

ZH: 她偏爱穿白色的衣服。
EN: She favors wearing white clothes.

ZH: 他总是偏向拒绝帮助别人。
EN: He always tends to refuse to help others.

ZH: 我偏要去参加那个活动。
EN: I insist on participating in that event.

ZH: 老板偏好与经验丰富的员工合作。
EN: The boss prefers working with experienced employees.

ZH: 她偏向于阅读小说而非传记。
EN: She tends to prefer reading novels over biographies.
